  <front>
   <head>SONNET.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Now, young-ey'd Spring, on gentle breezes borne,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">'Mid the deep woodlands, hills, and vales, and bowers,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Unfolds her leaves, her blossoms, and her flowers,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Pouring their soft luxuriance on the morn.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O! how unlike the wither'd, wan, and worn,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And limping Winter, that o'er russet moors,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And plashy fields, and ice-incrusted shores</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Strays, — and commands his rising winds to mourn!</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Protracted Life, thou art ordain'd to wear</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A form like his; — and, shou'd thy gifts be mine,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I tremble lest a kindred influence drear</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Steal on my mind; — but pious Hope benign,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Soul's new day-spring, shall avert the fear,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And gild Existence in her dim decline.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
